ieee8021BridgeEvbMib.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbMib

revisions.description: Published as part of IEEE Std 802.1Q 2014 revision. Cross references updated and corrected. ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIMvFormat added. ieee8021BridgeEvbVsiMgrID16 added and ieee8021BridgeEvbVsiMgrID deprecated. ieee8021BridgeEvbVDPCounterDiscontinuity description clarified. Conformance and groups fixed. Fixed maintenance item to IEEE Std 802.1Qbg-2012.
Initial version published in IEEE Std 802.1Qbg.

ieee8021BridgeEvbMib.contactinfo: WG-URL: http://www.ieee802.org/1 WG-EMail: stds-802-1@ieee.org Contact: IEEE 802.1 Working Group Chair Postal: C/O IEEE 802.1 Working Group IEEE Standards Association 445 Hoes Lane Piscataway NJ 08854 USA E-mail: STDS-802-1-L@LISTSERV.IEEE.ORG
ieee8021BridgeEvbMib.description: The EVB MIB module for managing devices that support Ethernet Virtual Bridging. Unless otherwise indicated, the references in this MIB module are to IEEE Std 802.1Q-2014. Copyright (C) IEEE (2014). This version of this MIB module is part of IEEE802.1Q; see the draft itself for full legal notices.

ieee8021BridgeEvbSysType.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbSysType
ieee8021BridgeEvbSysType.description: The evbSysType determines if this is an EVB Bridge or EVB station.

ieee8021BridgeEvbSysNumExternalPorts.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbSysNumExternalPorts
ieee8021BridgeEvbSysNumExternalPorts.description: The evbSysNumExternalPorts parameter indicates how many externally accessible port are available.

ieee8021BridgeEvbSysEvbLldpTxEnable.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbSysEvbLldpTxEnable
ieee8021BridgeEvbSysEvbLldpTxEnable.description: This object is used to initialize the LLDP EVB objects for new SBPs and URPS. When set to 'true' a new SBP or URP will place the local EVB objects in the LLDP nearest Customer database; when set to 'false' a new SBP or URP will not place the local EVB objects in the LLDP database.

ieee8021BridgeEvbSysEvbLldpManual.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbSysEvbLldpManual
ieee8021BridgeEvbSysEvbLldpManual.description: This object is used to initialize the LLDP EVB objects for new SBPs and URPS. When set to 'false' the operating configuration will be determined by the comparison between the local and remote LLDP EVB objects (automatic), regardless of the setting of ieee8021BridgeEvbSysLldpTxEnable. When ieee8021BridgeEvbSysLldpManual is 'true' the configuration will be determined by the setting of the local EVB objects only (manual).

ieee8021BridgeEvbSysEvbLldpGidCapable.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbSysEvbLldpGidCapable
ieee8021BridgeEvbSysEvbLldpGidCapable.description: The value of this object is used as the default value of the BGID or SGID bit of the EVB LLDP TLV string.

ieee8021BridgeEvbSysEcpAckTimer.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbSysEcpAckTimer
ieee8021BridgeEvbSysEcpAckTimer.description: A value indicating the Bridge Proposed ECP ackTimer.

ieee8021BridgeEvbSysEcpDfltAckTimerExp.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbSysEcpDfltAckTimerExp
ieee8021BridgeEvbSysEcpDfltAckTimerExp.description: The exponent of 2 indicating the Bridge Proposed ECP ackTimer in tens of microseconds.

ieee8021BridgeEvbSysEcpMaxRetries.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbSysEcpMaxRetries
ieee8021BridgeEvbSysEcpMaxRetries.description: A value indicating the Bridge ECP maxRetries.

ieee8021BridgeEvbSysVdpDfltRsrcWaitDelay.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbSysVdpDfltRsrcWaitDelay
ieee8021BridgeEvbSysVdpDfltRsrcWaitDelay.description: A value indicating the Bridge Resource VDP Timeout.

ieee8021BridgeEvbSysVdpDfltRsrcWaitDelay.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbSysVdpDfltRsrcWaitDelayExp
ieee8021BridgeEvbSysVdpDfltRsrcWaitDelay.description: The exponent of 2 indicating the Bridge Resource VDP Timeout in tens of microseconds.

ieee8021BridgeEvbSysVdpDfltReinitKeepAli.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbSysVdpDfltReinitKeepAlive
ieee8021BridgeEvbSysVdpDfltReinitKeepAli.description: A value indicating the Bridge Proposed VDP Keep Alive Timeout.

ieee8021BridgeEvbSysVdpDfltReinitKeepAli.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbSysVdpDfltReinitKeepAliveExp
ieee8021BridgeEvbSysVdpDfltReinitKeepAli.description: The exponent of 2 indicating the Bridge Proposed VDP Keep Alive Timeout in tens of microseconds.

ieee8021BridgeEvbSbpTable.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbSbpTable
ieee8021BridgeEvbSbpTable.description: A table that contains Station-facing Bridge Port (SBP) details.

ieee8021BridgeEvbSbpEntry.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbSbpEntry
ieee8021BridgeEvbSbpEntry.description: A list of objects describing SBP.

ieee8021BridgeEvbSbpLldpManual.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbSbpLldpManual
ieee8021BridgeEvbSbpLldpManual.description: The evbSbpLldpManual parameter switches EVB TLVs to manual mode. In manual mode the running parameters are determined solely from the local LLDP database values.

ieee8021BridgeEvbSbpVdpOperRsrcWaitDelay.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbSbpVdpOperRsrcWaitDelay
ieee8021BridgeEvbSbpVdpOperRsrcWaitDelay.description: The value used to initialize the waitWhile timer (41.5.5.7) by the station VDP state machine when the state machine is waiting for a response.

ieee8021BridgeEvbSbpVdpOperRsrcWaitDelay.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbSbpVdpOperRsrcWaitDelayExp
ieee8021BridgeEvbSbpVdpOperRsrcWaitDelay.description: The exponent of 2 used to calculate the value to initialize the waitWhile timer (41.5.5.7) by the station VDP state machine when the state machine is waiting for a response.

ieee8021BridgeEvbSbpVdpOperReinitKeepAli.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbSbpVdpOperReinitKeepAlive
ieee8021BridgeEvbSbpVdpOperReinitKeepAli.description: The value used to initialize the waitWhile timer (41.5.5.5) by the station VDP state machine in order to determine when to transmit a keep alive message.

ieee8021BridgeEvbSbpVdpOperReinitKeepAli.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbSbpVdpOperReinitKeepAliveExp
ieee8021BridgeEvbSbpVdpOperReinitKeepAli.description: The exponent of 2 used to calculate the value to initialize the waitWhile timer (41.5.5.5) by the station VDP state machine in order to determine when to transmit a keep alive message.

ieee8021BridgeEvbSbpVdpOperToutKeepAlive.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbSbpVdpOperToutKeepAlive
ieee8021BridgeEvbSbpVdpOperToutKeepAlive.description: The value used to initialize the waitWhile timer (41.5.5.13) by the EVBCB VDP state machine in order to determine when to transmit a keep alive message.

ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIDBTable.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIDBTable
ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIDBTable.description: A table that contains database of the active Virtual Station Interfaces.

ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIDBEntry.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIDBEntry
ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIDBEntry.description: A list of objects containing database of the active Virtual Station Interfaces.

ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIComponentID.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIComponentID
ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIComponentID.description: The evbVSIComponentID is the ComponentID for the C-VLAN component of the EVB Bridge or for the edge relay of the EVB station.

ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIPortNumber.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIPortNumber
ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIPortNumber.description: The evbVSIPortNumber is the Port Number for the SBP or URP where the VSI is accessed.

ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIIDType.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIIDType
ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIIDType.description: This object specifies the VSIID Type for the VSIID in the DCN

ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIID.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIID
ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIID.description: This object specifies the VSIID that uniquely identifies the VSI in the DCN

ieee8021BridgeEvbVSITimeSinceCreate.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbVSITimeSinceCreate
ieee8021BridgeEvbVSITimeSinceCreate.description: This object specifies the time since creation

ieee8021BridgeEvbVsiVdpOperCmd.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbVsiVdpOperCmd
ieee8021BridgeEvbVsiVdpOperCmd.description: This object identifies the type of TLV.

ieee8021BridgeEvbVsiOperRevert.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbVsiOperRevert
ieee8021BridgeEvbVsiOperRevert.description: The evbOperRevert status indicator shows the most recent value of the KEEP indicator from the VDP protocol exchange.

ieee8021BridgeEvbVsiOperHard.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbVsiOperHard
ieee8021BridgeEvbVsiOperHard.description: The evbVsiHard status indicator shows the most recent value of the HARD indicator from the VDP protocol exchange.

ieee8021BridgeEvbVsiOperReason.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbVsiOperReason
ieee8021BridgeEvbVsiOperReason.description: This object indicates the outcome of a request.

ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIMgrID.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIMgrID
ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIMgrID.description: This object identifies the VSI Manager with a database that holds the detailed VSI type and or instance definitions.

ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIType.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIType
ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIType.description: The VTID is an integer value used to identify a pre-configured set of controls and attributes that are associated with a set of VSIs.

ieee8021BridgeEvbVSITypeVersion.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbVSITypeVersion
ieee8021BridgeEvbVSITypeVersion.description: The VSI Type Version is an integer identifier designating the expected/desired VTID version. The VTID version allows a VSI Manager Database to contain multiple versions of a given VSI Type, allowing smooth migration to newer VSI types.

ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIMvFormat.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIMvFormat
ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIMvFormat.description: This object specifies the MAC/VLAN format. basic - Basic MAC/VLAN format partial - Partial MAC/VLAN format vlanOnly - Vlan-only MAC/VLAN format

ieee8021BridgeEvbVSINumMACs.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbVSINumMACs
ieee8021BridgeEvbVSINumMACs.description: This object specifies the the number of MAC address/VLAN ID pairs contained in the repeated portion of the MAC/VLANs field in the VDP TLV.

ieee8021BridgeEvbVDPMachineState.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbVDPMachineState
ieee8021BridgeEvbVDPMachineState.description: This object specifies the VDP state machine.

ieee8021BridgeEvbVDPCommandsSucceeded.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbVDPCommandsSucceeded
ieee8021BridgeEvbVDPCommandsSucceeded.description: This object specifies the VDP number of successful commands since creation.

ieee8021BridgeEvbVDPCommandsFailed.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbVDPCommandsFailed
ieee8021BridgeEvbVDPCommandsFailed.description: This object specifies the VDP number of failed commands since creation

ieee8021BridgeEvbVDPCommandReverts.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbVDPCommandReverts
ieee8021BridgeEvbVDPCommandReverts.description: This object specifies the VDP command reverts since creation

ieee8021BridgeEvbVDPCounterDiscontinuity.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbVDPCounterDiscontinuity
ieee8021BridgeEvbVDPCounterDiscontinuity.description: The time (in hundredths of a second) since the last counter discontinuity for any of the counters in the row.

ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIMgrID16.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIMgrID16
ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIMgrID16.description: This object identifies the VSI Manager with a database that holds the detailed VSI type and or instance definitions.

ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIFilterFormat.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIFilterFormat
ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIFilterFormat.description: This object specifies the MAC/VLAN format: vid (see 41.2.9.1) macVid (see 41.2.9.2) groupidVid (see 41.2.9.3) groupidMacVid (see 41.2.9.4)

ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIDBMacTable.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIDBMacTable
ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIDBMacTable.description: A table that contains database of the active Virtual Station Interfaces.

ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIDBMacEntry.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIDBMacEntry
ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIDBMacEntry.description: A list of objects containing database of the MAC/VLANs associated with Virtual Station Interfaces.

ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIMac.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIMac
ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIMac.description: The mac-address part of the MAC/VLANs for a VSI.

ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIVlanId.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIVlanId
ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIVlanId.description: The Vlan ID part of the MAC/VLANs for a VSI.

ieee8021BridgeEvbUAPConfigTable.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbUAPConfigTable
ieee8021BridgeEvbUAPConfigTable.description: A table that contains configuration parameters for UAP.

ieee8021BridgeEvbUAPConfigEntry.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbUAPConfigEntry
ieee8021BridgeEvbUAPConfigEntry.description: A list of objects containing information to configure the attributes for UAP.

ieee8021BridgeEvbUAPComponentId.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbUAPComponentId
ieee8021BridgeEvbUAPComponentId.description: The ComponentID of the port for the UAP.

ieee8021BridgeEvbUAPPort.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbUAPPort
ieee8021BridgeEvbUAPPort.description: The port number of the port for the UAP.

ieee8021BridgeEvbUapConfigIfIndex.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbUapConfigIfIndex
ieee8021BridgeEvbUapConfigIfIndex.description: The value of the instance of the IfIndex object, defined in the IF-MIB, for the interface corresponding to this port, or the value 0 if the port has not been bound to an underlying frame source and sink.

ieee8021BridgeEvbUAPSchAdminCDCPRole.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbUAPSchAdminCDCPRole
ieee8021BridgeEvbUAPSchAdminCDCPRole.description: The administratively configured value for the local port's role parameter. The value of AdminRole is not reflected in the S-channel TLV. The AdminRole may take the value S or B. S indicates the sender is unwilling to accept S-channels configuration (mode, # channels supported, channel index) from its neighbor and that the sender is willing to accept SVID assignments from the neighbor. Stations usually take the S role. B indicates the sender is willing to accept S-channels configuration (mode, # channels supported, channel index) from its neighbor and that the sender is willing do the best it can to fill the SVID assignments from the neighbor. Bridges usually take the B role.

ieee8021BridgeEvbUAPSchAdminCDCPChanCap.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbUAPSchAdminCDCPChanCap
ieee8021BridgeEvbUAPSchAdminCDCPChanCap.description: The administratively configured value for the Number of Channels supported parameter. This value is included as the ChanCap parameter in the S-channel TLV.

ieee8021BridgeEvbUAPSchOperCDCPChanCap.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbUAPSchOperCDCPChanCap
ieee8021BridgeEvbUAPSchOperCDCPChanCap.description: The operational value for the Number of Channels supported parameter. This value is included as the ChnCap parameter in the S-channel TLV.

ieee8021BridgeEvbUAPSchAdminCDCPSVIDPool.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbUAPSchAdminCDCPSVIDPoolLow
ieee8021BridgeEvbUAPSchAdminCDCPSVIDPool.description: Determines the lowest S-VIDs available for assignment by CDCP.

ieee8021BridgeEvbUAPSchAdminCDCPSVIDPool.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbUAPSchAdminCDCPSVIDPoolHigh
ieee8021BridgeEvbUAPSchAdminCDCPSVIDPool.description: Determines the highest S-VIDs available for assignment by CDCP.

ieee8021BridgeEvbUAPSchOperState.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbUAPSchOperState
ieee8021BridgeEvbUAPSchOperState.description: The current runnning state of CDCP.

ieee8021BridgeEvbSchCdcpRemoteEnabled.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbSchCdcpRemoteEnabled
ieee8021BridgeEvbSchCdcpRemoteEnabled.description: CDCP state for the remote S-channel.

ieee8021BridgeEvbSchCdcpRemoteRole.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbSchCdcpRemoteRole
ieee8021BridgeEvbSchCdcpRemoteRole.description: The value for the remote port's role parameter.

ieee8021BridgeEvbUAPConfigStorageType.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbUAPConfigStorageType
ieee8021BridgeEvbUAPConfigStorageType.description: The storage type for this row. Rows in this table that were created through an external process may have a storage type of readOnly or permanent. For a storage type of permanent, none of the columns have to be writable.

ieee8021BridgeEvbUAPConfigRowStatus.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbUAPConfigRowStatus
ieee8021BridgeEvbUAPConfigRowStatus.description: RowStatus for creating a UAP table entry.

ieee8021BridgeEvbCAPConfigTable.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbCAPConfigTable
ieee8021BridgeEvbCAPConfigTable.description: A table that contains configuration information for the S-Channel Access Ports (CAP).

ieee8021BridgeEvbCAPConfigEntry.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbCAPConfigEntry
ieee8021BridgeEvbCAPConfigEntry.description: A list of objects containing information for the S-Channel Access Ports (CAP)

ieee8021BridgeEvbSchID.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbSchID
ieee8021BridgeEvbSchID.description: This object represents the SVID for a ieee8021BridgeEvbSysType of evbBridge and a SCID(S-Channel ID) for a ieee8021BridgeEvbSysType of evbStation.

ieee8021BridgeEvbCAPComponentId.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbCAPComponentId
ieee8021BridgeEvbCAPComponentId.description: Component ID for S-channel Access Port.

ieee8021BridgeEvbCapConfigIfIndex.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbCapConfigIfIndex
ieee8021BridgeEvbCapConfigIfIndex.description: The value of the instance of the IfIndex object, defined in the IF-MIB, for the interface corresponding to this port, or the value 0 if the port has not been bound to an underlying frame source and sink. The underlying IfEntry indexed by this column MUST be persistent across reinitializations of the management system.

ieee8021BridgeEvbCAPPort.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbCAPPort
ieee8021BridgeEvbCAPPort.description: Port number for the S-Channel Access Port.

ieee8021BridgeEvbCAPAssociateSBPOrURPCom.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbCAPAssociateSBPOrURPCompID
ieee8021BridgeEvbCAPAssociateSBPOrURPCom.description: Component ID of the Server Edge Port to be associated with the CAP.

ieee8021BridgeEvbCAPAssociateSBPOrURPPor.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbCAPAssociateSBPOrURPPort
ieee8021BridgeEvbCAPAssociateSBPOrURPPor.description: Port number of the Server Edge Port to be associated with the CAP.

ieee8021BridgeEvbURPTable.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbURPTable
ieee8021BridgeEvbURPTable.description: A table that contains configuration information for the Uplink Relay Ports(URP).

ieee8021BridgeEvbURPEntry.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbURPEntry
ieee8021BridgeEvbURPEntry.description: A list of objects containing information for the Uplink Relay Ports(URP).

ieee8021BridgeEvbURPComponentId.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbURPComponentId
ieee8021BridgeEvbURPComponentId.description: Component ID that the URP belongs to.

ieee8021BridgeEvbURPIfIndex.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbURPIfIndex
ieee8021BridgeEvbURPIfIndex.description: The value of the instance of the IfIndex object, defined in the IF-MIB, for the interface corresponding to this port, or the value 0 if the port has not been bound to an underlying frame source and sink. It is an implementation specific decision as to whether this object may be modified if it has been created or if 0 is a legal value. The underlying IfEntry indexed by this column MUST be persistent across reinitializations of the management system.

ieee8021BridgeEvbURPBindToISSPort.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbURPBindToISSPort
ieee8021BridgeEvbURPBindToISSPort.description: The evbURPBindToISSPort is the ISS Port Number where the URP is attached. This binding is optional and only required in some systems.

ieee8021BridgeEvbURPLldpManual.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbURPLldpManual
ieee8021BridgeEvbURPLldpManual.description: The evbUrpLldpManual parameter control how the EVB TLV determines the operating values for parameters. When set TRUE only the local EVB TLV will be used to determine the parameters.

ieee8021BridgeEvbURPVdpOperRsrcWaitDelay.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbURPVdpOperRsrcWaitDelay
ieee8021BridgeEvbURPVdpOperRsrcWaitDelay.description: The parameter evbURPVdpOperRsrcWaitDelay is the exponent of 2 used to set the VDP resourceWaitDelay timer at the EVB Bridge.

ieee8021BridgeEvbURPVdpOperRsrcWaitDelay.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbURPVdpOperRsrcWaitDelayExp
ieee8021BridgeEvbURPVdpOperRsrcWaitDelay.description: The parameter evbURPVdpOperRsrcWaitDelay is the exponent of 2 used to set the VDP resourceWaitDelay timer at the EVB Bridge.

ieee8021BridgeEvbURPVdpOperRespWaitDelay.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbURPVdpOperRespWaitDelay
ieee8021BridgeEvbURPVdpOperRespWaitDelay.description: The evbUrpVdpOperRespWaitDelay is how long a EVb station VDP will wait for a response from the EVB Bridge VDP.

ieee8021BridgeEvbURPVdpOperReinitKeepAli.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbURPVdpOperReinitKeepAlive
ieee8021BridgeEvbURPVdpOperReinitKeepAli.description: The evbURPVdpOperReinitKeepAlive is the exponent of 2 used to determine the time interval of Keep Alives transmitted by the EVB station.

ieee8021BridgeEvbURPVdpOperReinitKeepAli.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbURPVdpOperReinitKeepAliveExp
ieee8021BridgeEvbURPVdpOperReinitKeepAli.description: The evbURPVdpOperReinitKeepAlive is the exponent of 2 used to determine the time interval of Keep Alives transmitted by the EVB station.

ieee8021BridgeEvbEcpTable.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbEcpTable
ieee8021BridgeEvbEcpTable.description: A table that contains configuration information for the Edge Control Protocol (ECP).

ieee8021BridgeEvbEcpEntry.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbEcpEntry
ieee8021BridgeEvbEcpEntry.description: A list of objects containing information for theEdge Control Protocol (ECP).

ieee8021BridgeEvbEcpOperAckTimerInit.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbEcpOperAckTimerInit
ieee8021BridgeEvbEcpOperAckTimerInit.description: The initial value used to initialize ackTimer (43.3.6.1).

ieee8021BridgeEvbEcpOperAckTimerInitExp.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbEcpOperAckTimerInitExp
ieee8021BridgeEvbEcpOperAckTimerInitExp.description: The initial value used to initialize ackTimer. Expressed as exp where 10*2exp microseconds is the duration of the ack timer(43.3.6.1).

ieee8021BridgeEvbEcpOperMaxRetries.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbEcpOperMaxRetries
ieee8021BridgeEvbEcpOperMaxRetries.description: This integer variable defines the maximum number of times that the ECP transmit state machine will retry a transmission if no ACK is received.

ieee8021BridgeEvbEcpTxFrameCount.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbEcpTxFrameCount
ieee8021BridgeEvbEcpTxFrameCount.description: The evbECPTxFrameCount is the number of ECP frame transmitted since ECP was instanciated.

ieee8021BridgeEvbEcpTxRetryCount.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbEcpTxRetryCount
ieee8021BridgeEvbEcpTxRetryCount.description: The evbECPTxRetryCount is the number of times ECP re-tried transmission since ECP was instanciated.

ieee8021BridgeEvbEcpTxFailures.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbEcpTxFailures
ieee8021BridgeEvbEcpTxFailures.description: The evbECPTxFailures is the number of times ECP failed to successfully deliver a frame since ECP was instanciated.

ieee8021BridgeEvbEcpRxFrameCount.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbEcpRxFrameCount
ieee8021BridgeEvbEcpRxFrameCount.description: The evbECPRxFrameCount is the number of frames received since ECP was instanciated.

ieee8021BridgeEvbSysGroup.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbSysGroup
ieee8021BridgeEvbSysGroup.description: The collection of objects used to represent a EVB management objects.

ieee8021BridgeEvbSbpGroup.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbSbpGroup
ieee8021BridgeEvbSbpGroup.description: The collection of objects used to represent a SBP management objects.

ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIDBGroup.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIDBGroup
ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIDBGroup.description: The collection of objects used to represent a EVB VSI DB table.

ieee8021BridgeEvbUAPGroup.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbUAPGroup
ieee8021BridgeEvbUAPGroup.description: The collection of objects used to represent a EVB UAP table.

ieee8021BridgeEvbCAPConfigGroup.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbCAPConfigGroup
ieee8021BridgeEvbCAPConfigGroup.description: The collection of objects used to represent a EVB CAP management objects.

ieee8021BridgeEvbsURPGroup.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbsURPGroup
ieee8021BridgeEvbsURPGroup.description: The collection of objects used to represent a EVBS URP management objects.

ieee8021BridgeEvbEcpGroup.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbEcpGroup
ieee8021BridgeEvbEcpGroup.description: The collection of objects used to represent a EVB CAP management objects.

ieee8021BridgeEvbSysV2Group.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbSysV2Group
ieee8021BridgeEvbSysV2Group.description: The collection of objects used to represent a EVB management objects.

ieee8021BridgeEvbSbpV2Group.description: The collection of objects used to represent a SBP management objects.

ieee8021BridgeEvbVSIDBV2Group.description: The collection of objects used to represent a EVB VSI DB table.

ieee8021BridgeEvbsURPV2Group.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbsURPV2Group
ieee8021BridgeEvbsURPV2Group.description: The collection of objects used to represent a EVBS URP management objects.

ieee8021BridgeEvbEcpV2Group.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbEcpV2Group
ieee8021BridgeEvbEcpV2Group.description: The collection of objects used to represent a EVB CAP management objects.

ieee8021BridgeEvbbCompliance.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbbCompliance
ieee8021BridgeEvbbCompliance.description: The compliance statement for devices supporting EVB as defined in IEEE 802.1Q.

ieee8021BridgeEvbsCompliance.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbsCompliance
ieee8021BridgeEvbsCompliance.description: The compliance statement for devices supporting EVBS as defined in IEEE 802.1Q.

ieee8021BridgeEvbbComplianceV2.name: ieee8021BridgeEvbbComplianceV2
ieee8021BridgeEvbbComplianceV2.description: The compliance statement for devices supporting EVB as defined in IEEE 802.1Q.

ieee8021BridgeEvbsComplianceV2.description: The compliance statement for devices supporting EVBS as defined in IEEE 802.1Q.
